    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="300"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/2132</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BRW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 12, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.46 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4765. Have received telegram from Luxemburg signed <persName>Emile
                        Reuter</persName>, Minister of State, of which following is translation:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Luxemburg Chamber in order of the day, voted unanimously in its session
                            of October 8, has invited the Government of the Grand Duchy to urge the
                            President of the United States to support our claims and our rights as
                            an independent state at the time of the peace negotiations. I beg Your
                            Excellency kindly to telegraph this resolution to President <persName
                                corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName> and to intercede so that wish
                            expressed by representatives of country [with] which the Luxemburg
                            Government eagerly associates itself may be granted.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BRW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
